<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-146-204 </DOCNO><DOCID>10 806 320</DOCID><JOURNAL>The Seybold Report on Publishing Systems  May 29 1991 v20 n17p33(2)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Seybold Publications Inc. 1991.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Npath. (Company-by-Company Preview) (Npath Inc.'s Tableworks tableeditor) (American Newspaper Publishers Association TechnicalExposition and Conference 1991)andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT>Company:   Npath Inc. (Products).andO;Product:   Tableworks (Add-in/on software) (Marketing).andO;Topic:     Add-In/On SoftwarePrinting IndustryPromotion of ProductDesktop Publishing.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>Npath.andP;  Npath's Tableworks is a table editor that is integrated with Xpress3.0 to provide extensive capabilities for automating table layout.andP;  Now inbeta testing, it is due for a June release at a price of $249.andM;Table cells in Tableworks are made from Xpress boxes, so the user has accessto all Xpress style and formatting abilities during table development.andO;Tables of any complexity can be created by splitting and merging cells, rowsor columns.andP;  The size and location of all table elements can be automaticallyadjusted when the user resizes a portion of the table.andP;  Tableworks can alsoauto-size the table continuously as the user enters text.andM;Npath is also working on a version called Tableworks Pro, which will supportthe creation of very long tables using tab-delimited text.andP;  It will includefeatures such as slanted row and column headers, direct import of data invarious database and spreadsheet formats, and automatic adjustment of thetable layout according to the contents of individual table cells.andP;  TableworksPro is slated for a September release at a price of $859.andO;</TEXT></DOC>